The paper also discusses the use of NOMA for uplink transmissions, which is relevant to the study of networking and internet architecture. 

3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of coordinated and non-coordinated transmissions in NOMA, which involves the design and analysis of control systems. The paper also discusses the use of successive interference cancellation (SIC) at the receiver, which is a control system technique used to mitigate co-channel interference.
